Insider Activity


Individual




Jeffrey W. Greenberg



Mr. Jeffrey W. Greenberg is Chairman & Chief Executive Officer at Aquiline Capital Partners LLC and Chairman at Conning Holdings Corp. He is on the Board of Directors at Validus Holdings Ltd., NewYork-Presbyterian Hospital and The Metropolitan Museum of Art. He is also co-founder of Aquiline Capital Partners. He is a member of the Association of the Bar of the City of New York, the Council on Foreign Relations, and a fellow of the Foreign Policy Association. He is a member of the board of overseers of Weill Cornell Medical College.
Prior to co-founding Aquiline Capital Partners in 2005, Mr. Greenberg was the chairman and chief executive officer of Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. Where he began his career before joining American International Group and FUTURITY First Insurance Group, Inc. After serving in numerous executive positions at AIG, he rejoined MMC as chief executive officer of MMC Capital.
Mr. Greenberg earned an A.B. from Brown University and a J.D. from Georgetown University.



